Pfizer raises dividend by nearly 6%, stock gains

Pfizer Inc. PFE, -0.68% said Monday it was raising its dividend by 5.6%, as the dividend yield stays more than double its health-care peer group. The new quarterly dividend of 38 cents a share, up from 36 cents a share, will be payable March 6, 2020 to shareholders of record on Jan. 31. Based on Friday's stock closing price of $38.33, the new annual dividend rate implies a yield of 3.97%, compared with the yield for the SPDR Health Care Select Sector ETF XLV, -1.11% of 1.48% and the yield for the SPDR S&P 500 ETF SPY, -1.84% of 1.73%. Pfizer's stock, which rose 0.4% in premarket trading, has lost 12.2% year to date through Friday, while the Dow Jones Industrial Average DJIA, -2.29% has gained 20.6%.